==English==

===Etymology===
Abbreviation of ''Hoochinoo'', a group of Alaskan Indians who made liquor.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːtʃ|-uːtʃ]]

===Noun===
'''hooch'''
# ''(Informal)'' Alcoholic [[liquor]], especially inferior or illicit [[whisky]].
# ''(Military Slang)'' A [[thatch|thatched]] hut, or any simple dwelling.

